/* ==========================================================================
   DigiTimber DarkTheme (DTDT) - Your custom overrides

   Any CSS placed in this file will be loaded AFTER dark-blend.css on every
   admin page (assuming dark mode is active). Use this for your own tweaks
   that should survive module updates - this file is never overwritten on
   upgrade.

   NOTE: When the dark/light toggle is enabled, custom.css loads in BOTH
   modes (dark and light). If you want rules that only apply in dark mode,
   scope them based on the presence of the dark stylesheet. The dark
   stylesheet has id="dtdt-css" so you can use a :has selector:

     body:has(link#dtdt-css) .my-element {
         color: var(--color-text-strong);
     }

   Or simply reference the CSS tokens - they only resolve when dark-blend.css
   is loaded, so rules using `var(--color-dark-2)` etc. naturally only apply
   in dark mode.

   Examples:

     .my-custom-hook {
         background: var(--color-dark-3);
     }

     Override a specific token globally:
     :root {
         --color-link: #7dd3fc;
     }

   Tokens you can reuse are defined at the top of dark-blend.css.
   ========================================================================== */
